obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (6802)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6802&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Repatriation of Prisoners Act,`
  line 2003.
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 1st January, 2004, vide notification No. S.O. 1464(E), dated 24th December, 2003, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (6803)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6803&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "contracting State" means a Government of any country or place outside India in respect of`
  line `which arrangement has been made by the Central Government with the Government of such country`
  line `or place through a treaty or otherwise for transfer of prisoners from India to such country or place and`
  line `vice versa and includes any other Government of such country or place specified by the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, under sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "prisoner" means a person undergoing a sentence of imprisonment under an order passed by a`
  line `criminal court including the courts established under the law for the time being in force in contracting`
  line States;
  line
  line `(d) "warrant" means a warrant issued under sub-section (1) of section 7 or sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 12, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(e) words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (6804)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Application of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6804&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that the provisions of this Act shall apply to a country or place outside India as may be specified in`
  line `the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) If the notification under sub-section (1) relates to a country or place outside India with which a`
  line `treaty has been entered into by India for the transfer of prisoners between that country and India, then,`
  line `such notification shall also set out the full text of the said treaty and shall in no case remain in force`
  line `longer than the period of the said treaty.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Central Government is of the opinion that, with respect to a country or place outside India,`
  line `provisions of this Act require to be modified to give effect to a treaty in relation to such country, it may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that the application of this Act to such country shall be`
  line `subject to such conditions, exceptions and modifications specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (6805)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Application for transfer by a prisoner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6805&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Any prisoner who is a citizen of a contracting State may`
  line `make an application to the Central Government for transfer of his custody from India to that contracting`
  line `State:`
  line
  line `Provided that if a prisoner is not able to make an application himself because of his ill health, mental`
  line `condition, old age or being a minor, then, the application may be made by any other person entitled to act`
  line `on his behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (6806)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Consideration of request by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 6 of 2011, s. 2, for "martial law" (w.e.f. 1-4-2011).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6806&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of the application under`
  line `section 4, the Central Government shall direct the officer in charge of the prison, where the prisoner is`
  line `confined, to furnish such information which in the opinion of that Government is relevant for the purpose`
  line `of transfer.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the information under sub-section (1), if the Central Government is satisfied that—`
  line
  line `(a) no inquiry, trial or any other proceeding is pending against the prisoner;`
  line
  line `(b) death penalty has not been awarded to the prisoner;`
  line
  line `(c) the prisoner has not been convicted for an offence under the ^1`
  line `[military law]; and`
  line
  line `(d) transfer of custody of the prisoner to the contracting State shall not be prejudicial to the`
  line `sovereignty, security or any other interest of India,`
  line `it shall pass an order for forwarding the application of the prisoner to the contracting State.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (6807)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Comments of contracting State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6807&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The application of the prisoner shall be forwarded by the`
  line `Central Government through prescribed means to the Government of the contracting State to deal with`
  line `such application along with the following information, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a copy of the judgment and a copy of the relevant provisions of the law under which the`
  line `sentence has been passed against the prisoner;`
  line
  line `(b) the nature, duration and date of commencement of the sentence of the prisoner;`
  line
  line `(c) medical report or any other report regarding the antecedents and character of the prisoner,`
  line `where it is relevant for the disposal of his application or for deciding the nature of his confinement;`
  line and
  line
  line `(d) any other information which the Central Government may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any application of a prisoner forwarded by the Central Government has been accepted by`
  line `the contracting State, the Central Government may seek from such contracting State, all or any of the`
  line `following information or documents before taking decision to transfer the prisoner to the contracting`
  line `State, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a statement or document indicating that the prisoner is a citizen of the contracting State;`
  line
  line `(b) a copy of the relevant law of the contracting State constituting the act or omission as the`
  line `offence, on account of which the sentence has been passed in India, as if such act or omission was an`
  line `offence under the law of that State;`
  line
  line `(c) a statement of the fact or any law or regulation relating to the duration and enforcement of the`
  line `sentence of the prisoner in the contracting State upon his transfer;`
  line
  line `(d) the willingness of the contracting State to accept the transfer of the prisoner and an`
  line `undertaking to administer the remaining part of the sentence of the prisoner;`
  line
  line `(e) an undertaking to comply with the conditions, if any, specified by the Central Government;`
  line and
  line
  line `(f) any other information or document which the Central Government may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (6808)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Consideration of request by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6808&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government, on receipt of`
  line `a communication from the concerned contracting State,—`
  line
  line `(a) expressing its willingness to accept the transfer of the prisoner; and`
  line
  line `(b) undertaking to comply with the conditions specified in the warrant,`
  line
  line `is satisfied that the prisoner should be transferred to the said State, the Central Government may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, issue a warrant in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 8 in such form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a warrant is issued under sub-section (1), the Central Government shall inform the`
  line `contracting State accordingly and request that State to specify the person to whom and the place within`
  line `India where custody of the prisoner shall be delivered.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (6809)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Provision to issue warrant for transfer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6809&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall authorise an officer`
  line `not below the rank of a Joint Secretary to a State Government, within the limits of whose jurisdiction the place of imprisonment of the prisoner is situated, to issue a warrant on behalf of the Central Government`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 7 directing the officer in charge of the prison therein to deliver the custody`
  line `of the prisoner to the person authorised by the contracting State to which the prisoner is to be transferred,`
  line `presenting such person a copy of the warrant together with all the records relating to the prisoner and the`
  line `personal effects taken from the prisoner at the time of his admission in the prison.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the presentation of a warrant referred to in sub-section (1), the officer in charge of the prison`
  line `shall forthwith comply with the warrant and obtain thereon the signature of the person to whom delivery`
  line `of the prisoner, records and the personal effects relating to the prisoner to be removed from the prison is`
  line given.
  line
  line `(3) After delivery of the prisoner to the person authorised by the contracting State under sub-section`
  line `(2), the officer in charge of the prison transferring the prisoner shall forward a copy of the warrant to the`
  line `court which committed the prisoner to the prison, along with a statement that the prisoner has been`
  line `delivered to the person authorised by the contracting State under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The delivery of the prisoner in compliance of the warrant issued under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `discharge the officer in charge of the prison from the responsibility of keeping the prisoner in his custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (6810)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Operation of warrant and retaking prisoner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6810&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for the person authorised by the`
  line `contracting State to whom the custody of a prisoner is delivered under the provisions of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 8 to receive and hold in custody such prisoner and to convey him out of India and if the prisoner`
  line `escapes from such custody within India, the prisoner may be arrested without warrant by any person who`
  line `shall without undue delay deliver such prisoner to the officer in charge of the nearest police station and the`
  line `prisoner so arrested shall be liable for committing an offence under section 224 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860) and shall also be liable for such sentence of imprisonment in India which he would have to`
  line `undergo if the delivery of custody of such prisoner had not been made under section 8.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (6811)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Transfer of record.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6811&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Where a prisoner is or is to be transferred to a contracting State under the`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Central Government may requisition the records of any proceeding, including`
  line `judicial proceedings relating to that prisoner from any court or office, and may direct that such records`
  line `shall be sent to the Government of the contracting State.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (6812)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power of court and Central Government shall not be affected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6812&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The transfer of a prisoner`
  line `from India to a contracting State shall not affect the power of the court which passed the judgment to`
  line `review its judgment and power of the Central Government or State Government to suspend, remit or`
  line `commute the sentence in accordance with any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (6813)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Transfer into India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6813&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may accept the transfer of a prisoner, who is`
  line `a citizen of India, from a contracting State wherein he is undergoing any sentence of imprisonment`
  line `subject to such terms and conditions as may be agreed to between India and that State.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Central Government accepts the request for a transfer under sub-section (1), then,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, it may issue a warrant to`
  line `detain the prisoner in prison in accordance with the provisions of section 13 in such form as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (6814)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Determination of prison and issue of warrant for receiving transfer in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6814&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government shall, in consultation with a State Government, determine the prison situated within`
  line `the jurisdiction of such State Government where the prisoner with respect to whom a warrant has been`
  line `issued under sub-section (2) of section 12, shall be lodged and the officer who shall receive and hold him`
  line `in custody.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall authorise any officer not below the rank of a Joint Secretary to that`
  line `Government to issue a warrant under sub-section (2) of section 12 and to direct the officer referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) to receive and hold the prisoner, with respect to whom the warrant is issued, in custody.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be lawful for the officer referred to in sub-section (1) to receive and hold in custody any`
  line `prisoner delivered to him under the direction made in the warrant issued under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section12 and to convey such prisoner to any prison determined under sub-section (1) for being dealt with`
  line `in accordance with the said warrant and if the prisoner escapes from such custody, the prisoner may be`
  line `arrested without warrant by any person who shall without undue delay deliver such prisoner to the officer in charge of the nearest police station and the prisoner so arrested shall be liable for committing an`
  line `offence under section 224 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and shall also be liable to be dealt with in`
  line `accordance with the said warrant.`
  line
  line `(4) A warrant under sub-section (2) of section 12 shall provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the bringing of the prisoner into India from a contracting State or a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(b) the taking of such prisoner in any part of India being a place at which effect may be given to`
  line `the provisions contained in the warrant;`
  line
  line `(c) the nature and duration of imprisonment of the prisoner in accordance with the terms`
  line `and conditions referred to in sub-section (1) of section 12 and the imprisonment of such prisoner in`
  line `Indiain such manner as may be contained in the warrant; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the imprisonment`
  line `of a prisoner in compliance with a warrant issued under sub-section (2) of section 12 shall be deemed to`
  line `be imprisonment under a sentence of a court competent to pass such a sentence of imprisonment in India.`
  line
  line `(6) If the sentence of imprisonment passed against the prisoner in the contracting State is`
  line `incompatible with the Indian law as to its nature, duration or both, the Central Government may, by order,`
  line `adapt the sentence of such punishment as to the nature, duration or both, as the case may be, as is`
  line `compatible to the sentence of imprisonment provided for a similar offence had that offence been`
  line `committed in India:`
  line
  line `Provided that the sentence so adapted shall, as far as possible, correspond with the sentence imposed`
  line `by the judgment of the contracting State to the prisoner and such adapted sentence shall not aggravate the`
  line `punishment, by its nature, duration or both in relating to the sentence imposed in the contracting State.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (6815)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6815&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the means through which an application may be forwarded under sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the form in which a warrant may be issued under sub-section (1) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) the form in which a warrant may be issued under sub-section (2) of section 12; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which may be prescribed under clause (d) of sub-section (4) of section 13.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (6816)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Laying of rules, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6816&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Every notification issued under sub-sections (1) and (3) of section 3 and`
  line `every rule made under section 14 shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of`
  line `Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the`
  line `notification or rule or both Houses agree that the notification or rule should not be made, the notification`
  line `or rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that notification or rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (6817)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830&sectionId=6817&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00018_200349_1517807324830
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
